
@startuml
' STEP 1: Basic Stock, Customers, Orders

class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -vatNumber: String
}

class Product {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -stockLevel: int
}

class Order {
  -id: int
  -customer: Customer
  -orderLines: List<OrderLine>
  -isPaid: boolean
  -isShipped: boolean
  -paymentDate: Date
  -shippingDate: Date
}

class OrderLine {
  -id: int
  -product: Product
  -quantity: int
  -isShipped: boolean
}

Customer "1" --> "0..*" Order
Order "1" --> "0..*" OrderLine
OrderLine "1" --> "1" Product

note right of Order
  Each order must be paid before shipping.
  An order is shipped only if all lines are available in stock.
end note

note right of OrderLine
  An order line is marked as shipped when the product is delivered.
end note

' STEP 2: Partial Shipments

OrderLine "1" --> "1" ShipmentLine
class ShipmentLine {
  -id: int
  -shipment: Shipment
  -orderLine: OrderLine
  -status: String <<enumeration>> {Pending, Shipped, Delivered, Damaged}
}

class Shipment {
  -id: int
  -dateShipped: Date
  -dateReceived: Date
  -deliveryStatus: String <<enumeration>> {Pending, InTransit, Delivered, Damaged}
}

Shipment "1" --> "0..*" ShipmentLine

note right of OrderLine
  Order lines can be shipped individually or in groups.
end note

note right of Shipment
  Each shipment may contain multiple order lines.
  Track delivery status for each shipment.
end note

' STEP 3: Multiple Addresses, Invoicing Options

Customer "1" --> "1" Address
class Address {
  -id: int
  -street: String
  -city: String
  -postcode: String
  -isHeadOffice: boolean
}

Customer "1" --> "0..*" Invoice
class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -order: Order
  -dueDate: Date
  -isPaid: boolean
  -paymentMethod: String <<enumeration>> {Prepaid, Postpaid}
}

Order "1" --> "1" Invoice

note right of Customer
  A customer has a head office address and possibly multiple delivery addresses.
end note

note right of Invoice
  Payment method can be Prepaid (paid at order time) or Postpaid (paid after delivery).
end note

' STEP 4: Grouped Shipments & Delivery Tracking

ShipmentLine "1" --> "1" DeliveryEvent
class DeliveryEvent {
  -id: int
  -shipmentLine: ShipmentLine
  -eventDate: Date
  -eventType: String <<enumeration>> {Packed, Shipped, Received, Damaged}
}

ShipmentLine "1" --> "0..*" DeliveryEvent

note right of DeliveryEvent
  Track the lifecycle of each shipment line with events:
  Packed -> Shipped -> Received / Damaged
end note

note right of Shipment
  Shipments may be grouped by order lines for efficient handling.
end note

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Classes and Relationships:

- **Customer**
  - Attributes: id, name, address, vatNumber
  - Associations: 1 to * Orders, 1 to * Invoices, 1 to * Addresses

- **Address**
  - Attributes: id, street, city, postcode, isHeadOffice

- **Product**
  - Attributes: id, name, stockLevel

- **Order**
  - Attributes: id, customer, orderLines, isPaid, isShipped, paymentDate, shippingDate
  - Associations: 1 to * OrderLines, 1 to 1 Invoice

- **Invoice**
  - Attributes: id, order, dueDate, isPaid, paymentMethod
  - Associations: 1 to 1 Order

- **OrderLine**
  - Attributes: id, product, quantity, isShipped
  - Associations: 1 to 1 Product, 1 to * ShipmentLines

- **Shipment**
  - Attributes: id, dateShipped, dateReceived, deliveryStatus
  - Associations: 1 to * ShipmentLines

- **ShipmentLine**
  - Attributes: id, shipment, orderLine, status
  - Associations: 1 to 1 Shipment, 1 to 1 OrderLine, 1 to * DeliveryEvents

- **DeliveryEvent**
  - Attributes: id, shipmentLine, eventDate, eventType

---

